<p>When selecting a solar installer in Jacksonville, it's crucial to choose companies with proper Florida licensing, including an electrical contractor license and solar contractor certification. Look for installers with extensive experience in Florida's climate conditions and familiarity with JEA's interconnection requirements. Top-quality installers should offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels, 10-15 years for inverters) and workmanship (minimum 5-10 years). Verify that potential contractors carry proper insurance, provide detailed written proposals with system specifications, and have strong local references. Many of Jacksonville's best solar companies are certified by major manufacturers like Tesla, SunPower, and LG, and maintain certifications from the North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners (NABCEP). Always obtain multiple quotes and ensure the installer will handle all permitting and JEA interconnection paperwork.</p>

